  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7 and peel the garlic</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> the cauliflower into small, bite-size florets and add to 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> baking tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> with 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> whole garlic cloves (save the rest for later) and 2-3 tbsp olive oil</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> generously with salt and pepper and roast for 30-40 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, peel and cut the onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;into 2cm wedges</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> and halve the shallots</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> a pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> olive oil over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> hot, add the onion and shallot with a large pinch of salt and cook for 4 min or until slightly softened&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, add the lentils to a pot with plenty of cold water, bring to the boil, then cook on a low heat for 25-30 mins or until tender</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the balsamic vinegar, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> sugar and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> water to the onions</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reduce</strong> the heat to its lowest setting and cook the onions, covered, for a further 20-25min or until they&rsquo;re sweet and sticky</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, add the hazelnuts to a small baking dish</p>\r\n<p><strong>Put</strong> it in the oven for 7-9 min or until they've darkened slightly in colour and are starting to crack</p>\r\n<p><strong>Set</strong> the toasted hazelnuts aside to cool</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, zest the lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Chop</strong> the parsley (stems too) and the remaining garlic finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Chop</strong> the cooled hazelnuts finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Combine</strong> everything in a bowl for serving - this is your gremolata</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Drain</strong> the cooked lentils, then return them to the pot</p>\r\n<p><strong>Dress</strong> them with a dash of olive oil, a squeeze of lemon juice and season generously with salt and pepper</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Tip:</strong></span> Cut the remaining lemon into wedges for serving!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> the cauliflower is fork tender, blitz the cauliflower and garlic in a food processor with a drizzle of olive oil (and a knob of butter if you&rsquo;re not vegan) until smooth</p>\r\n<p><strong>Taste</strong> and season generously with salt and pepper</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>Tip:</strong></span> For a smoother mash, add more olive oil or a splash of milk (if you're not vegan)</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/552.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
